                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13997451" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 14 May 2014 10:30:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi - should a CXF jetty transport property be introduced to enable the same endpoint URL for multiple handlers ? By default it is disabled, if the property is set then it is OK ? Willem, would it work for you ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers, Sergey&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13998489" author="jpell" created="Thu, 15 May 2014 06:20:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I too would like to see this particular code backed out and made optional.  It certainly broke quite a few things when we upgraded, so much so that I backed out the upgrade and am still running 2.7.10.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking forward to 2.7.12 with the ability to opt in to this feature.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13998744" author="xushichang" created="Thu, 15 May 2014 13:06:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes lets have a property to control this behavior&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14005587" author="njiang" created="Thu, 22 May 2014 03:57:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Desmon,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5610&quot; title=&quot;Jetty transport should warn the user if the endpoint address conflicts with published service&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-5610&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-5610&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was intended to avoiding the user publish the two services with exactly same address.&lt;br/&gt;
And I cruise to know what kind of user case that you need to publish the mulitple services with the same address.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can add a system property to disable the check if you still need to register multiple handlers with same endpoint url.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Willem&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14005599" author="xushichang" created="Thu, 22 May 2014 04:27:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Willem&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have two handlers serving the same endpoint url address - one is a jaxrs service bean and one is a static content service.&lt;br/&gt;
I would&apos;t have designed this kind of thing from the start, but unfortunately I have a bunch of apps that depend on this service doing exactly this - serving both dynamic jaxrs and static content on the same service endpoint. I&apos;d like to have the configurability  for this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you&lt;br/&gt;
Desmond&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14005942" author="dkulp" created="Thu, 22 May 2014 14:11:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Desmond,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you create a small testcase that shows how you have this all configured?   That would definitely help us understand how you have Jetty setup to dispatch to multiple things on the same URL.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;br/&gt;
Dan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14006020" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Thu, 22 May 2014 15:31:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi All, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Willem introduced an &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;org.apache.cxf.transports.http_jetty.DontCheckUrl&quot; system property, disabled by default.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers, Sergey&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14006660" author="jpell" created="Fri, 23 May 2014 00:44:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We use multiple org.eclipse.jetty.server.handler.AbstractHandler attached to the same address and can check the post parameters and even the content to decide to handle them or let the next handler in the chain handle them.  This is pretty standard jetty use case.  I think I can work around it, but would be easier not to have to.  So good to see a property, although would have been better if it were not a system property and instead a config parameter that could be passed into the jetty factory.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14008505" author="jpell" created="Mon, 26 May 2014 01:01:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we are going to be able to upgrade to 2.7.11 even with this feature.  So it&apos;s not so much of an issue for me anymore.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14008543" author="xushichang" created="Mon, 26 May 2014 03:36:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;simple test case attached CXF5740Demo&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14008544" author="xushichang" created="Mon, 26 May 2014 03:36:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the property, but I second that it should be set on the bus rather than a system property.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016447" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 12:30:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, thanks for attaching the example code. I&apos;ve added a single argument constructor accepting a Bus only to JettyHttpHandler. Can you please run your code against the trunk when you have a chance, make sure you have the same bus used to initialize JettyHttpDestinations and custom handlers...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers, Sergey&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14018481" author="xushichang" created="Thu, 5 Jun 2014 05:15:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Apologies - I haven&apos;t had trunk set up on my machine yet.&lt;br/&gt;
I looked at your latest change though; having the property also settable on the bus looks good too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14026236" author="njiang" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2014 08:11:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is the change that Sergey made.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=cxf.git;a=commit;h=4604c9fe25da4be126b54c0eb458f8f32503ac71&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=cxf.git;a=commit;h=4604c9fe25da4be126b54c0eb458f8f32503ac71&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14026448" author="njiang" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2014 13:51:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added the system property &quot;org.apache.cxf.transports.http_jetty.DontCheckUrl&quot; to skip the check of url path. Bus property setting is only support in CXF master branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
